### Returns the result of the requested bitwise operation.
### :param you: The other value to compare against.
### :returns: The resulting `S64` value.
routine S64.$bitand(you: S64) -> S64
  return bit_and[S64](me, you)

### Returns the result of the requested bitwise operation.
### :param you: The other value to compare against.
### :returns: The resulting `S64` value.
routine S64.$bitor(you: S64) -> S64
  return bit_or[S64](me, you)

### Returns the result of the requested bitwise operation.
### :param you: The other value to compare against.
### :returns: The resulting `S64` value.
routine S64.$bitxor(you: S64) -> S64
  return bit_xor[S64](me, you)

### Returns the result of the requested bitwise operation.
### :returns: The resulting `S64` value.
routine S64.$bitnot() -> S64
  return bit_xor[S64](me, -1)

